================================================================
PRACTICAL 6(b) - Extract Data from Excel into DataTable and Vice Versa
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Easy-Medium

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will read an Excel file into a DataTable, display it, 
modify it, and write it back to a new Excel sheet.

--- STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS ---

PART 1 - SETUP

Step 1: Use the same "students.xlsx" file from 6(a),
        or create a new Excel file with:
        A1: ID    B1: Name    C1: Score
        A2: 1     B2: Alice   C2: 85
        A3: 2     B3: Bob     C3: 90
        A4: 3     B4: Charlie C4: 78
        Save as "marks.xlsx" on Desktop.

Step 2: Open UiPath Studio → New Project.
  - Name it: Practical_6b_DataTable
  - Click Create

PART 2 - EXCEL TO DATATABLE (Read)

Step 3: Drag an "Excel Application Scope" activity into the sequence.
  - WorkbookPath: path to "marks.xlsx"

Step 4: Inside the scope, drag "Read Range" activity.
  - SheetName: "Sheet1"
  - Range: "" (reads all data)
  - AddHeaders: checked (tick this checkbox)
  - Output → DataTable: press Ctrl+K → name it: dtMarks

Step 5: After the Excel Application Scope, drag an "Output Data Table" activity.
  - DataTable: dtMarks
  - Output → Text: press Ctrl+K → name it: strOutput

Step 6: Drag a "Message Box" activity.
  - Text: strOutput
  - Run (F5) → You should see a table with all 3 students and their scores.

PART 3 - MODIFY THE DATATABLE

Step 7: Drag a "For Each Row" activity after the Output Data Table.
  - In: dtMarks
  - Inside the For Each Row body, drag an "Assign" activity.
    - Left side:  CurrentRow("Score")
    - Right side: CInt(CurrentRow("Score")) + 5
  - This adds 5 bonus marks to each student's score.

PART 4 - DATATABLE TO EXCEL (Write back)

Step 8: Drag another "Excel Application Scope" after the For Each Row loop.
  - WorkbookPath: same "marks.xlsx" path

Step 9: Inside this scope, drag "Write Range" activity.
  - SheetName: "Sheet2"
  - StartingCell: "A1"
  - DataTable: dtMarks
  - AddHeaders: checked

Step 10: Run (F5).
  - Open "marks.xlsx" → click on Sheet2
  - You should see the updated scores (each score +5) written there.

EXPECTED OUTPUT in Sheet2:
  ID    Name      Score
  1     Alice     90
  2     Bob       95
  3     Charlie   83
